The overall construction program was originally estimated at a term of 15 months, reserving an additional margin of 3 months for the final closing of the sale deeds. The entire execution of the project costs is audited monthly through the reports of an independent Quantity Surveyor who acts as technical monitor (Project Monitor). The first report issued by this independent professional revalidates the full viability of the developer's budget, confirming that the works can be completed without material deviations from the declared costs.

Developer Solvency and Guarantee Protection Scheme

The comprehensive development and material execution of the works is carried out by Meeko Construction Limited, a construction and development company wholly owned and managed by the professional Ryan Meehan. The developer has extensive experience of 20 years within the construction industry, having carried out his professional activity in both Ireland and Australia. The company has operated with its own consolidated corporate structure in Irish territory since 2017, with a direct workforce of more than 20 full-time employees. While the firm accumulates an extensive track record in the execution of single-family residential contracts and large-scale commercial works, the current project represents its first multi-residential development carried out under the dual condition of builder and developer, a strategy aimed at integrating property development as the central line of its business.

